│ THOUGHT: The issue is that LLVM's instcombine pass is incorrectly           │
│ optimizing GEP (GetElementPtr) equality comparisons when the data layout    │
│ has small pointer sizes (p:8:8:8 means 8-bit pointers). The optimization    │
│ assumes that if two GEPs with the same base and type produce equal          │
│ pointers, then their indices must be equal. However, with 8-bit pointers,   │
│ pointer arithmetic wraps around modulo 256, so different indices can        │
│ produce the same pointer value due to overflow. I need to find where this   │
│ optimization is implemented and add a check to prevent it when pointer      │
│ arithmetic may wrap.                                                        │
